{{!
    @template block_workload/modal_done

    Minimal standalone document loaded into the manage-page modal iframe
    after a modal form completes. Intentionally rendered WITHOUT the Moodle
    header/footer: the page must stay tiny, and core_renderer::footer()
    would consume the session notifications queued for the parent page
    (they must survive until the parent reloads). Because there is no page
    footer, AMD is unavailable and a raw script tag is used — the same
    approach as core_privacy/htmlpage. The "wl_modal_done" token is the
    contract with the block_workload/manage AMD module (initList message
    listener).

    @package   block_workload
    @copyright 2026 Yurii Lysak
    @license   http://www.gnu.org/copyleft/gpl.html GNU GPL v3 or later

    Example context (json):
    {}
}}
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>{{#str}} managetitle, block_workload {{/str}}</title>
</head>
<body>
<script>window.parent.postMessage("wl_modal_done", "*");</script>
</body>
</html>
